    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Update on Your Senior Developer Application\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you for taking the time to attend the final round of interviews for the Senior Developer position at [Company]. We truly appreciated the depth of your insights and the enthusiasm you brought to our conversation. After careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate for this role.\n\nWe want to assure you that this decision was made with great care and that we were impressed by your qualifications. We received an overwhelming number of applications for this position, and it was a truly challenging call to choose the best fit among so many strong contenders. Sifting through a massive crowd of applicants, we were delighted to see the quality of talent that applied, and we hope this email conveys how intense the volume was. We will keep your profile in mind for future opportunities that align with your skills, and we wish you the very best in your continued career journey.\n\nSincerely,  \n[Your Name]  \n[Your Title]  \n[Company Name]\n\n*Note: This email is crafted to be professional and kind while clearly closing the application process, leaving no room for negotiation or further discussion.*",
